==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydracid
<hw>Hy*drac"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hydr-</ets> +
<ets>acid</ets>: cf. F. <ets>hydracide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An acid containing hydrogen; -- sometimes applied to distinguish
acids like hydrochloric, hydrofluoric, and the like, which contain no
oxygen, from the oxygen acids or oxacids. See <er>Acid</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydracrylic</ent>⟦br⟧
